parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description: ClientToken is an idempotency token that ensures a call to CreateProfile completes only once. You choose the value to pass. For example, an issue might prevent you from getting a response from CreateProfile. In this case, safely retry your call to CreateProfile by using the same CreateProfile parameter value. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: Tags
parameters.description: A list of the tag keys and values that you want to associate with the Route 53 Profile. (dict) --- Tag for the Profile. Key associated with the Tag. Value for the Tag.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Profile.

nested_items.name: ClientToken
nested_items.description: The ClientToken value that was assigned when the Profile was created.

nested_items.name: CreationTime
nested_items.description: The date and time that the Profile was created, in Unix time format and Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

nested_items.name: ModificationTime
nested_items.description: The date and time that the Profile was modified, in Unix time format and Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

nested_items.name: OwnerId
nested_items.description: Amazon Web Services account ID of the Profile owner.

nested_items.name: StatusMessage
nested_items.description: Status message that includes additiona information about the Profile.
